From: OnePlus Nord CE5 Kernel Workflow <kernel@local>
Date: 2026-06-08
Subject: [PATCH] module: load stock vendor_dlkm modules despite MODVERSIONS/vermagic mismatch

PROBLEM (observed on device, dmesg/logcat with the recompiled GKI kernel flashed):
  The recompiled GKI Image (with KernelSU-Next + SUSFS + extra features, built
  with a different LOCALVERSION / toolchain / .config than the OEM kernel) has
  different per-symbol CRCs (CONFIG_MODVERSIONS=y) and a different vermagic
  string than the OEM kernel the stock vendor_dlkm .ko modules were built
  against. As a result the in-kernel module loader rejects the stock vendor
  modules:

    <module>: disagrees about version of symbol <sym>      (check_version -> CRC)
    <module>: version magic 'X' should be 'Y'  -> -ENOEXEC  (same_magic -> vermagic)

  Because oplus_bsp_hybridswap_zram.ko (the vendor driver that owns /dev/zram0
  and exposes /sys/block/zram0/hybridswap_meminfo) lives in the *stock*
  vendor_dlkm and is NOT rebuilt by this workflow, it failed to load -> zram /
  hybrid_swap / RAM-expansion stayed dead.

FIX:
  Make the two module-version gates in kernel/module/version.c unconditionally
  accept the module, so every stock vendor .ko loads on the recompiled GKI image
  regardless of MODVERSIONS CRC or vermagic differences.

    - check_version(): always return 1 (skip the per-symbol CRC comparison).
    - same_magic():    always return 1 (skip the vermagic string comparison).

  This is safe here because:
    * The GKI KMI keeps the exported-symbol ABI stable, so the CRC/vermagic
      delta is a build-time artifact of the different LOCALVERSION/toolchain,
      not a real ABI break (all the other vendor modules already proved KMI
      compatibility by loading fine on the device).
    * CONFIG_MODULE_SIG_FORCE is not set, so module signature is advisory only;
      no extra signing gate blocks the stock modules.

  Equivalent in spirit to `modprobe --force-vermagic --force-modversion`, but
  applied kernel-wide so init/ueventd auto-loading of vendor_dlkm modules works.

NOTE: loading modules built for a different kernel will taint the kernel
(TAINT_FORCED_MODULE). That is expected and harmless for this use case.

--- a/kernel/module/version.c
+++ b/kernel/module/version.c
@@ -13,44 +13,19 @@ int check_version(const struct load_info *info,
 		  const char *symname,
 			 struct module *mod,
 			 const s32 *crc)
 {
-	Elf_Shdr *sechdrs = info->sechdrs;
-	unsigned int versindex = info->index.vers;
-	unsigned int i, num_versions;
-	struct modversion_info *versions;
-
-	/* Exporting module didn't supply crcs?  OK, we're already tainted. */
-	if (!crc)
-		return 1;
-
-	/* No versions at all?  modprobe --force does this. */
-	if (versindex == 0)
-		return try_to_force_load(mod, symname) == 0;
-
-	versions = (void *)sechdrs[versindex].sh_addr;
-	num_versions = sechdrs[versindex].sh_size
-		/ sizeof(struct modversion_info);
-
-	for (i = 0; i < num_versions; i++) {
-		u32 crcval;
-
-		if (strcmp(versions[i].name, symname) != 0)
-			continue;
-
-		crcval = *crc;
-		if (versions[i].crc == crcval)
-			return 1;
-		pr_debug("Found checksum %X vs module %lX\n",
-			 crcval, versions[i].crc);
-		goto bad_version;
-	}
-
-	/* Broken toolchain. Warn once, then let it go.. */
-	pr_warn_once("%s: no symbol version for %s\n", info->name, symname);
+	/*
+	 * OnePlus Nord CE5 (OOS16) workflow patch:
+	 * Accept any module regardless of symbol CRC (MODVERSIONS) mismatch so
+	 * that stock vendor_dlkm modules (e.g. oplus_bsp_hybridswap_zram.ko)
+	 * built against the OEM kernel still load on this recompiled GKI image.
+	 * The GKI KMI guarantees ABI stability for the exported symbol set, so
+	 * a CRC delta here is a build-time artifact, not a real ABI break.
+	 */
+	(void)info;
+	(void)symname;
+	(void)mod;
+	(void)crc;
 	return 1;
-
-bad_version:
-	pr_warn("%s: disagrees about version of symbol %s\n", info->name, symname);
-	return 0;
 }
 
 int check_modstruct_version(const struct load_info *info,
@@ -80,11 +55,15 @@ int check_modstruct_version(const struct load_info *info,
 int same_magic(const char *amagic, const char *bmagic,
 	       bool has_crcs)
 {
-	if (has_crcs) {
-		amagic += strcspn(amagic, " ");
-		bmagic += strcspn(bmagic, " ");
-	}
-	return strcmp(amagic, bmagic) == 0;
+	/*
+	 * OnePlus Nord CE5 (OOS16) workflow patch:
+	 * Always treat the vermagic as matching. The recompiled GKI image has a
+	 * different vermagic string (LOCALVERSION / compiler / config deltas)
+	 * than the OEM kernel the stock vendor modules were built against, which
+	 * would otherwise make module loading fail with -ENOEXEC
+	 * ("version magic '...' should be '...'"). Ignore the difference.
+	 */
+	return 1;
 }
 
